reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and looks great.
reviews.reviewText: Having built a lot of furniture with varying levels of coherence to the instructions, this one was a treat. The only screws that required a GREAT deal of elbow grease were the ones used to attach the doors. Otherwise, things went smoothly and it was done in about an hour. It looks great and the quality for the money is impressive. I will note that if you're very sensitive to smells, this does have a strong factory odor that lingers for about a week. If that sounds awful, pop the box open in an empty room and let it air out for a few days before you tackle it. It's been just a few weeks, but I love this little fella.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars CUTE CABINET FOR NOW
reviews.reviewText: This super cute cabinet was easy to put together, & although it isn't the most sturdy, it is functional & quite sweet to look at. I did not pay full price for it (like new), so I am pleased with my purchase. It may not last a decade, but it's made my bathroom much more organized for the time being.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars WAY too overpriced for terrible quality, but customer service is top notch!
reviews.reviewText: Original 2* review (posted 12/9/2022)-Since the pros list is shorter, I'll start with that...it was easy to put together. I am a fairly handy woman and usually put furniture together by myself... if I ever have to ask for my husband's help the item is either to heavy, awkward, or a nightmare to assemble; I didn't need to ask for his help in this case, it was incredibly simple.There's one neutral, it looks cheap, but I don't have it in the open so looks weren't that important to me.The cons... this is a BIG one! It is incredibly flimsy, I doubt it will last a year, I'm actually afraid to put cleaning supplies in it because it doesn't feel like it will be able to take any weight. I put the cleaning supplies on the very bottom self only, the other shelves are towels and sheets. The quality is terrible. I knew it wasn't going to be top of the line, I expected it, but I didn't expect it to be THIS bad... my cats have had corrugated cardboard scratch furniture that seems as sturdy as this. This should be priced MUCH lower, I would say $50 would be reasonable. I cannot recommend this to anyone, I would say find something of similar quality that is priced reasonably, or look for something the same price but much better quality, or pay $100 more and buy the solid wood furniture that's made in Vietnam, looks nice and should last for years (I bought both this and the solid wood furniture around the same time and was very impressed with the quality...I can't remember the name of that furniture, but will be leaving a review on it after this).Edited review 1/7/2023:I have to give major props to this company! THEY initiated contact to rectify my issues with their product 4 days ago (I never contacted them, all I did was write the review above). They offered either a replacement or a refund. I didn't see the email until today, so they ended up initiating a refund. I am incredibly impressed with their level of customer service!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great little cabinet!
reviews.reviewText: Make sure you measure your space. Came well packaged, no damaged pieces, no missing parts. Slight manufacturing smell, dissipated after a few days. More than enough storage for our foyer 1/2 bathroom. I am one of the most mechanically challenged people on the planet, took me a few hours to assemble, instructions are clear and easy to understand. My issue was me - figuring out best way to line up the holes for the door hinges and getting the screws in there while holding the door(s) up. Very good looking cabinet for the price and materials, just keep it dry!

reviews.reviewText: It said this was a easy assembly. However, it was not the instructions only had pictures did not include direction. Once you get it built properly and go through all the little twirks, it looks nice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Offers Tons of Storage!!
reviews.reviewText: Not only does this cabinet offers a decent amount of storage it fits in the nook of my hallway perfectly. I needed something useful but still nice to look at! I just ordered new knobs too because why not! It's a tiny bit wobbly but that might be user error. I'm a 5'7 140 pound woman and it took my about 2.5 hours to put together alone. The instructions were pretty straightforward and easy to understand. Overall great purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 2, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Don’t waste your time and money on this one
reviews.reviewText: I ordered this cabinet for a powder bathroom remodel to give some storage since it only has a pedestal sink. The cabinet looked cute in the pics and was in the budget I wanted to spend so I bought it. When it came, it was packed nicely and none of the pieces were damaged. The instructions were easy to read and follow although it is a picture diagram only with no words so make sure you do not miss any steps.So onto the actual building. The screws do not fit the holes properly and more than one would not lay flush especially when dealing with the hinges and the doors. The walls and top of the cabinet are held together with just a metal pin and a circular object that fits in a hole and spins around the pin to “lock” it into place however they do not lock it tight and the whole cabinet is wobbly due to the amount of play in it. The doors as mentioned earlier do on hang properly due to the screws not fitting flush in the holes leaving them wobbly as well. The doors are also held shut with just a strip of metal with a screw in the middle and a magnet and again, the screws would not lay flush and the metal closure tab spins making it impossible to close without adjusting every single time. That combined with crooked doors due to the improper fit screws, and you spend more time adjusting it than anyone should to open or close a single door.All over, this is a hot mess. It’s not sturdy and will not hold up over time. In fact, I’m afraid to even place a potted plant on it for fear it could fall if someone opens the doors with it on top. It’s that poorly made. If you are looking for something that will last awhile, this is just not it. I was tempted several times during building to just chuck it in the bin and not even try to finish it. It’s not worth the time or effort put into it and I’m still going to have to buy something else so it was a complete waste of money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for my hallway
reviews.reviewText: I have the tiniest linen closet and this cabinet is perfect for all my toiletries. It's stylish and fits in the space perfectly.

Very nice for the price! Clean and stylish. Cabinet is sturdy enough but was smaller than what we envisioned. Held plenty of items though and so is satisfactory for our needs. Very simple to assemble with easy to follow instructions! We definitely recommend this product.
